      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIGHTER COMMAND (5) did a great job in coming from this barrier for a resuming win by 2m over race rival BULLETPROOF BOY here last time out. That was his first start since September and he has won three of four second-up attempts so improvement is likely. Up to a distance where he has won four of six attempts. Can strike again. BAY OF BISCAY (6) hasn't raced since coming from the back row for fifth in October's Victoria Cup and he won the Eureka in Sydney two starts earlier. May give away fitness to some of these but he owns a good fresh record and has been readied with two trials, winning the latest. BULLETPROOF BOY (3) has 2m to make on FIGHTER COMMAND through the last-start second but he draws lower and was very good in his NSW stint prior, winning the G2 Newcastle Mile. JILLIBY WILLOW (1) has won four of seven attempts at this circuit and distance and the ace draw may see her competitive.",
